<p>Because an unpromoted silver can retreat more easily than a promoted one (see below), it is very common to leave a silver unpromoted at the far side of the board.</p>
<p><a name="Knight" id="Knight"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Shogi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Knight">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Knight</span></h3>
<p>A knight <i>jumps</i> at an angle intermediate between orthogonal and diagonal, amounting to one square forward plus one square diagonally forward, in a single motion. That is, it has a choice of two forward destinations. It cannot move to the sides or backwards.</p>
<table>
<tr>
<td>&#160;&#160;&#160;</td>
<td>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:102px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Shogi_knight.jpg" class="image" title="The knight"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dd/Shogi_knight.jpg/100px-Shogi_knight.jpg" width="100" height="104" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
