<p>It is often useful to leave a lance unpromoted (see below) at the far side of the board. However, since a lance cannot move backward or to the sides, it <i>must</i> promote if it arrives at the far rank.</p>
<p><a name="Pawn" id="Pawn"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Shogi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Pawn">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Pawn</span></h3>
<p>A pawn can move one square directly forward. It cannot retreat.</p>
<table>
<tr>
<td>&#160;&#160;&#160;</td>
<td>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:102px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Shogi_pawn.jpg" class="image" title="The pawn"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/Shogi_pawn.jpg/100px-Shogi_pawn.jpg" width="100" height="103" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Shogi_pawn.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The pawn</div>
</div>
</div>
</td>
<td>&#160;&#160;&#160;</td>
<td>
<table border="1" class="wikitable" style="width:107px; font-size:95%;">
<tr style="text-align:center;">
<td width="20">&#160;</td>
<td width="20">&#160;</td>
<td width="20">&#160;</td>
