<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Shogi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=23" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> The Japanese-language page <a href="http://shogi-pineapple.com/bbs/mibbs.cgi?mo=p&amp;fo=beginner&amp;tn=0006" class="external text" title="http://shogi-pineapple.com/bbs/mibbs.cgi?mo=p&amp;fo=beginner&amp;tn=0006" rel="nofollow">Shogi Pineapple</a> indicates the two orders; <i>ohashi</i> is depicted on the left and <i>ito</i> on the right. See also the page from <a href="http://www.luckydog.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/games/shogi/index.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.luckydog.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/games/shogi/index.htm" rel="nofollow">Lucky Dogs Games</a></li>
